pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Welfare reform has continued to progress since the submission of our response to the DWP review of exempt accommodation costs in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">July 2011.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We are concerned that no</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> formal response has been received or published </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">no</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> indication </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has been given regarding</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> where supported housing costs will sit in the recent Universal Credit consultation.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In December 2012 DWP announced that ren</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t for supported exempt accommodation was to be administered by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">local authority h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ousing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">enefit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> departments until 2017, when they are due to be abolished.  There is no clarity on the future administration of supported housing costs thereafter.  </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Not all su</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pported accommodation has been designated as ‘exempt’ </span><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e.g. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">situations </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">where</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> an agency manages the schemes separate to the landlord and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">where </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the landlord is a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">housing authority</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  Discretion appears to lie</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">enefit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">service</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is our view</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that contracted supported accommodation should be considered to be Universal Credit exempt and the acceptable level of rent charged for supported accommodation determined by the local authority.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is recognised that rents in this sector are higher than </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in other sectors due to the additional wear and tear in the property</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, additional security</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and higher management costs.  To include these rental costs within the current proposed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ceiling on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Universal Credit will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">make the scheme unaffordable and jeopardise t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he financial viability of such schemes.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A system that ensures the sustainability of supported housing has been recognised by various agencies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, including the Audit Commission,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> as cost effective in both economic and social terms, resulting from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reduction</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in health, social care and police intervention</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">To implement a system that does not adequately meet the cost of supported accommodation, resulting in a significant reduction in the provision of this type of housing, is likely </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">give rise to an</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> increase </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in domestic violence related injuries and deaths, more street homelessness</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, an increase in offending, increase in psychiatric </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">illness and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">hospital </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">admissions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in response to housing related stressors.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">With homelessness </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">expected</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to increase so will be the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> damaging effects of homelessness on individuals and their families</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  The adequate provision of affordable safe temporary homes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with support</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> will assist to identify and address the individual underlying causes of homelessness and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">prevent</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> repeat incidences </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of homelessness.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It should be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">acknowledged</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that people in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">supported</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> accommodation are normally linked </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">community and the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">area they live in and that familiarity is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">an integral </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">part of the support they are provided with.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The adequate provision of l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ocal affordable and secure supported accommodation is considered essential to ensure that these links are strengthened.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Available funding to cover </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">additional</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> housing management services should include the cost of concierge services to protect the security</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of the building and residents.  This service will meet the levels of risk that are currently high and expected to increase</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  It will enable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> clients with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> mental health problems</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to be managed in the community.  For probation schemes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">responsibility for high risk offenders appears to be increasing.  The ‘No Second Night Out’ </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">policy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">supports</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> rough sleepers, many of whom come with a high level of risk including substance misuse, offending, mental health and often a combination of these is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sues</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> are often users of supported accommodation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  In addition, attempts to be inclusive of and meet the needs of adults at risk of chronic social inclusion, some of whom have been in substance misuse treatment schemes multiple times, can be threatenin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">g, aggressive and sometimes violent and will require this level of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">additional housing management to protect the security of the property and residents</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">(i)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">the direct payment of housing costs to claimants</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The direct payment of housing costs to claimants sho</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">uld b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e excluded for supported exempt accommodation.  The nature of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">client group is likely to make it difficult to ensure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> regular</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> payment of rent.  </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">As the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">length of occupation is likely to be quite short, this will make recovery of rent arrears diffic</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ult, placing the financial viability of the scheme at risk.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  30 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>